  "original_title": "\u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bae\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0b87\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b9c\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bbe",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Ranil Wickramasinghe has resigned",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Parliamentary Secretary-General's written notice to the Chairman of the Election Commission regarding the vacancy in the Parliament due to the appointment of Ranil Wickramasinghe as President",
        "Parliamentary Secretary General Thammika Dasanayake has informed the Chairman of the Election Commission in writing that there is a vacancy in the post of Member of Parliament due to the inauguration of Member of Parliament Ranil Wickramasinghe as the President of the Democratic Socialist Republic of Sri Lanka.",
        "The Secretary General of the Parliament said that Ranil Wickramasinghe has informed him through a letter that he is accepting the office of the President of the country and will therefore resign from his position as a Member of Parliament with effect from 21st July 2022 i.e. from today.",
        "Pursuant to Article 66 (e) of the Constitution, the Secretary General of Parliament has notified the Chairman of the Election Commission under Section 64(5) of the Parliamentary Elections Act No. 1 of 1981, as amended by the Parliamentary Elections (Special Provisions) Act No. 35 of 1988, that a vacancy has occurred in the Ninth Parliament."
      ],
